{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Tit|1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","chapter":1,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:1:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":1,"verse":1,"text":"Paul, a servant of God and an apostle of Jesus Christ, for the faith of God’s elect and their knowledge of the truth that leads to godliness,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:1:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":1,"verse":2,"text":"in the hope of eternal life that God, who cannot lie, promised before time began.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:1:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":1,"verse":3,"text":"In his own time he has revealed his word in the preaching with which I was entrusted by the command of God our Savior:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:1:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":1,"verse":4,"text":"To Titus, my true son in our common faith. Grace and peace from God the Father and Christ Jesus our Savior.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:1:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":1,"verse":5,"text":"The reason I left you in Crete was to set right what was left undone and, as I directed you, to appoint elders in every town.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:1:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":1,"verse":6,"text":"An elder must be blameless, the husband of one wife, with faithful children who are not accused of wildness or rebellion.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:1:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":1,"verse":7,"text":"As an overseer of God’s household, he must be blameless, not arrogant, not hot-tempered, not an excessive drinker, not a bully, not greedy for money,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:1:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":1,"verse":8,"text":"but hospitable, loving what is good, sensible, righteous, holy, self-controlled,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:1:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":1,"verse":9,"text":"holding to the faithful message as taught, so that he will be able both to encourage with sound teaching and to refute those who contradict it.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:1:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":1,"verse":10,"text":"For there are many rebellious people, full of empty talk and deception, especially those from the circumcision party.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:1:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":1,"verse":11,"text":"It is necessary to silence them; they are ruining entire households by teaching what they shouldn’t in order to get money dishonestly.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:1:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":1,"verse":12,"text":"One of their very own prophets said, “Cretans are always liars, evil beasts, lazy gluttons.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:1:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":1,"verse":13,"text":"This testimony is true. For this reason, rebuke them sharply, so that they may be sound in the faith","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:1:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":1,"verse":14,"text":"and may not pay attention to Jewish myths and the commands of people who reject the truth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:1:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":1,"verse":15,"text":"To the pure, everything is pure, but to those who are defiled and unbelieving nothing is pure; in fact, both their mind and conscience are defiled.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:1:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":1,"verse":16,"text":"They claim to know God, but they deny him by their works. They are detestable, disobedient, and unfit for any good work.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","chapter":1,"paragraphStarts":[1,4,5,10,15],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Greeting"},{"beforeVerse":5,"text":"Titus’s Ministry in Crete"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:1:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Paul, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 13:9","book":"Act","chapter":13,"verse":9,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" a servant of God "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 16:17","book":"Act","chapter":16,"verse":17,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 1:1","book":"Rom","chapter":1,"verse":1,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Eph 6:6","book":"Eph","chapter":6,"verse":6,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jms 1:1","book":"Jas","chapter":1,"verse":1,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Pt 2:16","book":"1Pe","chapter":2,"verse":16,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rv 1:1","book":"Rev","chapter":1,"verse":1,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"text","text":" and an apostle of Jesus Christ, for "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Or according to"},{"kind":"text","text":" the faith of God’s elect "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"M